verbose_text: Notably, we found that beta-actin and alpha-tubulin protein levels were positively correlated with intrinsic growth rate (R = 0.12, p = 1.36 x 10 -5 and R = 0.02, p = 0.04, respectively), suggesting that their use in total protein load normalization as housekeeping proteins, rather than the median sample load normalization we performed, would have resulted in an erroneous adjustment for intrinsic growth rate differences between cell lines.
